        Gritty has also recently been featured in posts on a Neo-Nazi news website, in an apparent attempt to claim him for the US far-right, the Guardian reports.But unlike with other politicised memes, like Pepe the Frog, Gritty's wider popularity shows no sign of abating.Pepe the Frog 'is killed off' by creator He's earned name checks from comedian John Oliver, appeared alongside Ricky Gervais on The Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon and was recently featured in his own interview with Sports Illustrated magazine.From babies to dogs, homemade Gritty costumes were already a fan-favourite by Halloween.
    
      
              
